---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy & Terms of Use"
  description="Privacy Policy and Terms of Use for Luc Flynn's ad management services and resources."
>
  <style is:inline>
    .privacy-container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 4rem 2rem;
    }

    .privacy-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .privacy-header h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: 900;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-header p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-content {
      background: var(--dark-lighter);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 3rem;
    }

    .privacy-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-content h2:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .privacy-content h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .privacy-content p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-content ul {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-left: 2rem;
    }

    .privacy-content li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .privacy-content a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .privacy-container {
        padding: 2rem 1rem;
      }

      .privacy-content {
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }

      .privacy-header h1 {
        font-size: 2rem;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="privacy-container">
    <div class="privacy-header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy & Terms of Use</h1>
      <p>Last Updated: March 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-content">
      <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

      <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
      <p>We collect information that you provide directly to us, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name and email address when you download resources or sign up for services</li>
        <li>Company information and business details when you fill out forms</li>
        <li>Phone numbers if you choose to provide them</li>
        <li>Payment information when you purchase services (processed securely through Stripe)</li>
        <li>Communications you have with us via email or other channels</li>
        <li>Google Ads account data when you connect your Google Ads account to our tools (campaigns, ads, keywords, performance metrics, conversion data, and account settings)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide you with resources, tools, and services you request</li>
        <li>Send you educational content and updates about our services</li>
        <li>Respond to your questions and provide customer support</li>
        <li>Process payments and fulfill service agreements</li>
        <li>Improve our website and services</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        <li>Provide account monitoring, lead scoring, performance analysis, and historical comparisons through our software tools</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Information Sharing</h3>
      <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers who assist in operating our business (email services, payment processors, analytics providers)</li>
        <li>Professional advisors such as lawyers and accountants</li>
        <li>Law enforcement or regulatory agencies when required by law</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
      <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Understand how visitors use our website</li>
        <li>Remember your preferences</li>
        <li>Analyze website traffic and user behavior</li>
        <li>Track marketing campaign performance</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We use Google Tag Manager, Vercel Analytics, Hotjar, and PostHog for analytics. You can control cookies through your browser settings.</p>
      <p>We also use our own tracking pixel (EPI) on client websites to collect lead quality signals. This pixel collects: form submission data, IP-based location (city/region level only, not precise location), browser and device information, referral source, and UTM parameters. This data is used exclusively to score lead quality for the account holder who installed the pixel.</p>

      <h3>5. Data Security</h3>
      <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction. However, no internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h3>6. Your Rights</h3>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal information we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your information</li>
        <li>Opt-out of marketing communications at any time</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent where we rely on consent to process your data</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>7. Email Communications</h3>
      <p>When you provide your email address, you may receive:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Resources you requested (cheat sheets, playbooks, tools)</li>
        <li>Educational content related to paid advertising</li>
        <li>Information about our services and offers</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can unsubscribe from marketing emails at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in any email.</p>

      <h3>8. Children's Privacy</h3>
      <p>Our services are not directed to individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

      <h3>9. International Users</h3>
      <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in the United States or other countries where our service providers operate. By using our services, you consent to such transfers.</p>

      <h2>Google Ads Data Access</h2>

      <h3>What We Access</h3>
      <p>When you connect your Google Ads account to our tools (including but not limited to EPI, Media Buyer's Cockpit, and Snapshots), we access your Google Ads data through the Google Ads API. This includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Campaign settings, budgets, and bid strategies</li>
        <li>Ad group and keyword data</li>
        <li>Ad creative content and performance metrics</li>
        <li>Conversion tracking configuration and conversion data</li>
        <li>Account-level settings and change history</li>
        <li>Audience and targeting information</li>
        <li>Reporting data including spend, clicks, impressions, and conversions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We request only the data necessary to provide the specific tool's functionality. The scope of data accessed depends on which tool you are using.</p>

      <h3>How We Use Your Google Ads Data</h3>
      <p>Your Google Ads data is used exclusively to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Display your account data within our tools</li>
        <li>Generate performance reports and alerts</li>
        <li>Score lead quality (EPI)</li>
        <li>Monitor account health and detect issues (Cockpit)</li>
        <li>Create historical snapshots of account state for comparison (Snapshots)</li>
        <li>Provide recommendations and insights based on your account data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do NOT use your Google Ads data for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Advertising or marketing to you or others</li>
        <li>Selling or sharing with third parties for their own purposes</li>
        <li>Training machine learning models on your specific account data</li>
        <li>Any purpose unrelated to providing our tools and services to you</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How We Store Your Google Ads Data</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>OAuth tokens are encrypted at rest and stored securely</li>
        <li>Account data pulled from the API is stored in encrypted databases</li>
        <li>Historical snapshots are stored for the duration of your subscription</li>
        <li>Landing page screenshots and HTML captures are stored in encrypted cloud storage</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data Retention</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Active accounts: Data is retained for the duration of your subscription</li>
        <li>Cancelled accounts: Data is deleted within 30 days of account cancellation</li>
        <li>OAuth tokens: Revoked immediately upon disconnection or account cancellation</li>
        <li>You can request deletion of all your data at any time by contacting <a href="mailto:luc@lucflynn.com">luc@lucflynn.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Revoking Access</h3>
      <p>You can disconnect your Google Ads account from our tools at any time:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Through the settings page within any of our tools</li>
        <li>By revoking access in your Google Account permissions (myaccount.google.com/permissions)</li>
        <li>By contacting us at <a href="mailto:luc@lucflynn.com">luc@lucflynn.com</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>When you revoke access, we immediately stop accessing your Google Ads data and delete your OAuth tokens. Historical data already collected is retained per the Data Retention policy above unless you request its deletion.</p>

      <h3>Google API Services User Data Policy</h3>
      <p>Our use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.</p>

      <h2>Terms of Use</h2>

      <h3>1. Acceptance of Terms</h3>
      <p>By accessing or using this website and our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use our services.</p>

      <h3>2. Use of Services</h3>
      <p>You may use our website and services for lawful purposes only. You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
        <li>Infringe on intellectual property rights</li>
        <li>Transmit harmful code or malware</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems</li>
        <li>Use our services for spam or unsolicited communications</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Intellectual Property</h3>
      <p>All content on this website, including text, graphics, logos, and software, is the property of Luc Flynn or its licensors and is protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works without express written permission.</p>

      <h3>4. Free Resources</h3>
      <p>Free resources provided (cheat sheets, playbooks, calculators, etc.) are for your personal or business use. You may not resell, redistribute, or claim them as your own work.</p>

      <h3>5. Paid Services</h3>
      <p>When you purchase services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Payment is processed securely through Stripe</li>
        <li>Services will be delivered as described in the service agreement</li>
        <li>Refunds are subject to the specific refund policy stated at the time of purchase</li>
        <li>You are responsible for providing accurate information needed to deliver services</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>6. Disclaimers</h3>
      <p>Our services and resources are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not guarantee specific results from using our resources or services. Success in paid advertising depends on many factors outside our control.</p>

      <h3>7. Limitation of Liability</h3>
      <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, Luc Flynn shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of our services or resources.</p>

      <h3>8. Indemnification</h3>
      <p>You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Luc Flynn from any claims, damages, or expenses arising from your use of our services or violation of these terms.</p>

      <h3>9. Service Modifications</h3>
      <p>We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any aspect of our services at any time without notice.</p>

      <h3>10. Governing Law</h3>
      <p>These Terms of Use are governed by the laws of the United States. Any disputes will be resolved in the appropriate courts.</p>

      <h3>11. Changes to Terms</h3>
      <p>We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or Terms of Use, please contact us:</p>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:luc@lucflynn.com">luc@lucflynn.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
